reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 2, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars WIFI connection, not cable
reviews.reviewText: I was connecting 2 computers and a cell phone. Spun my wheels a lot trying to connect all three to work WIFI. Every time that I tried something, it printed several pages of instructions. Printing good until I tried printing photos. Could not print photos from Photoshop, Picture manager or any other program that I had used in the past. Operator error?I had to use HP Smart. Once I figured that out,I was OK. Colors print true to photo, unlike my old printer.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 8, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Worst printer I’ve had
reviews.reviewText: I have had other HP printers and this you use an app to scan. The app is horrible, can’t get my printer to show up have the time, every time I have to reattach it to my phone app it takes hours for it to finally connect. The pictures you print have a border around it so you don’t get an actual 4x5 or 8x10 without seeing a border in a frame. Can’t order ink at all through the app, will not connect when I select how I often I want ink. Wish I never bought this and waste of my money.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 9, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Bought at Walmart
reviews.reviewText: It’s a good product, you will have to update the software but you will have to do in on an android bc apple won’t let you, if you don’t update it you will struggle a lot. I bought it the first time and it said the ink cartridge wasn’t in there and I returned it, got another one and after setting it up putting paper in there it was saying that the tray was open, we spend almos 2 hrs trying to figure it out and after doing the update I haven’t had any problems with it. It is a bit slow but I got it for $50 I I’m not complaining about it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 31, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars What has happened to HP? Bought by the Chinese??
reviews.reviewText: This popped up when I gave this POS a 1 star. It says most of what I feel except for the awful language I used trying to operate this junk. I have used HP since the beginning of home computers. NO MORE.Poor design, cheaply built. Instructions are a joke. Constant paper jams. Internet connection may or may not work. Cute little buttons with symbols that mean nothing. I have had 6 HP printers over the years. Loved them. This is my last.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 20, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Never buy this
reviews.reviewText: This printer is a failure in every way. It was to come with ink jets, the color one never worked so spent another $30 to buy it. Tried printing with new ink jet and it came out horrible all 3 x/ finally gave up. The buttons are difficult to read/see. I strongly suggest a different printer. I wasted $ choosing this one

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 27, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Don't buy. I would give it no stars if I could.
reviews.reviewText: It gobble up ink. You can't print on glossy paper because the ink runs all over the page. I am considering giving this away to a thrift shop and buying a laser printer.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 9, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Never ever, ever, ever, ever buy an HP Printer again. I mean never.
reviews.reviewText: Have had this piece of crap for a year and recently they thought it would be a good idea to update the firmware so I could no longer use the ink cartridges I have been using. Evidently they are so proud of their cartridges that they are the only ones my cool printer will accept (wasn't that way last week). I will never buy anything from HP again. Hope they enjoy the money they got from this one.
